{"ok": true, "lean_translation": "import Mathlib


/-- Let H be the subgroup generated by two elements a, b of a group G. Prove that if a b=b a, then H is an abelian group. -/
theorem of_subgroup_of_commute {G : Type*} [Group G] (a b : G) (n1 n2 : ℕ) (h1 : a ^ n1 = b ^ n2) (h2 : b ^ n2 = a ^ n1) : ∀ x ∈ Subgroup.zpowers a ∩ Subgroup.zpowers b, ∀ y ∈ Subgroup.zpowers a ∩ Subgroup.zpowers b, x * y = y * x := by"}
